Description:  
    The server side is intended to run concurrenly from the client side.   
  
Install:  
    Create the server folder on your own machine.
    Copy the files in.
    CD into the directory and run: npm i express body-parder mongoose concurrently
                                   npm i -D nodemon  
                               
Startup: 
    In the server director run:    npm run server
  
Use: 
    You can make a GET request localhost:5000/api/user to get all users. 
    Make a POST request to the same URL to create a user. Note the content type is application/json
    I'd highly recommend taking 5 minutes to download Postman and "learn" it. 
    
DB Admin Access: 
    See the pinned message on discord. 
  

  
 
